@community_type
title: Community Type
subtitle: Understanding Your Community Context
new-page: true

Narration: Communities vary greatly depending on their setting and character. To get the right stakeholders involved, we need to understand what kind of community you're representing.

Narration: A maintenance robot rolls by, apparently trying to deliver mail to a fire hydrant. It's been at this for hours, convinced the hydrant is a very quiet resident.

- @rural_community: A rural community (farming, small towns, countryside)
- @urban_community: An urban community (city neighborhoods, districts)
- @mixed_community: A mixed community (suburban, small cities)

